column2: Busy boat traffic- Brian suffering from swimmer's itch- mystery snails- several loons sighted so far this summer.
Quiet day on the lake.  Gentle breeze- more particulates in water than last reading.
One other boat on the lake- calm- sunny day.  Hot - 90+ degrees.  Same particulates as last reading.
Mild breeze today.  Two other boats on the lake.  Several loons on the lake today.
Windy day- sunny and hot.  Four boats out on the lake.  Finally rained a little bit last night - very dry August so far!
Partly cloudy day.  Few white caps.  Wind out of the south-southwest.  Little activity on the lake this weekend.  1 Loon sighted.  (Brian)
Mostly sunny- mild winds out of the West-Southwest.  Busy Labor Day weekend.  Heavy boat activity.  1 loon sighted.  78 degrees.
Bright sunny day.  Light breeze.  No boats at all on the lake besides ours.  Water appears cloudy today.  Heavy rains the past few days.  65 degrees.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Partly sunny; 3 to 4 boats on the lake; breezy @ 10-20 mph; 75 degrees; clear water; no loons observed.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Clear water.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Sunny day; no wind; clear water. No loons observed.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Sunny day; clear water; no wind.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  No boats observed.  Partly sunny day; calm wind; 82 degrees; two pair of loons observed; greenish hue to the water.
Two loons observed on the lake.  Sunny day.  Light breeze.  Secchi measurement at 18.5 feet. Assisted by Beth Ihry.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Partly sunny day.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Sunny day.  Very hot.  No other boats on the lake. Observed three (3) loons on the lake.  Observed 1 Eagle flying over the lake.
Assisted by Beth Ihry.  Observed five (5) boats on the lake. No loons observed.  Sunny- hot day.
Sunny blue skies with minimal clouds. Slight breeze and only smooth water ripples. 66 degrees. Heavy Mayfly population in the air and surface of water.
Water appears slightly greener today. Moderately windy with small whitecaps forming. Many cabin owners up this weekend and several boats on the water.

Sunny blue skies with scattered white clouds. 82 degrees and windspeed 8mph. John (son-in-law) and I took measurements today.  Noticed Purple Loose Strife in a few areas on the lake - most heavily at NE end of lake close to boat landing.

Slight wind fron SW. Terre and I and friends Peter and Scherrie are out for a boat tour of the lake today. Sunny with no clouds- 76 degrees with moderate ripples on the water but no whitecaps forming. Slight wind from SW.  Observed 2 Bald Eagles flying overhead.  Believe that we have seen a total of 4 Eagles this year that circle the lake.  Had 5 inches of drenching rain yesterday and a total of 10 inches reported over the week.
